snippet.textDisplay: Hej Brad. I just felt like letting you know that it can work with the right item. Honestly you seem so pathetic in this video that I had to.The first and only time I dyed my hair was sort of accidental, sort of not. We had a project at school where we were supposed to recreate a photo and I got a bucket of water and paint thrown on my head. And since it was summer I just let it dry a bit and continued going to classes instead of washing it off like my classmates thought I should (I did wash my face). It started out being purple but became a very nice cherry blossom pink after a few weeks. Loved my hair the entire time. Have considered doing it again but I'm waiting until summer to decide.

snippet.textDisplay: Does nobody know that you can dye your hair with Koolaid. Let me tell you. My dad was so against crazy hair colors when I was a teen. My smart ass filled up a large pan with water and boiled it. I filled it up with 4 cherry Koolaid packages. And then dipped my whole head in the boiling water xD On dirty blonde/light brown natural hair color, it turned a deep red and smelled Amazing. 2years later I was bleaching my hair and the ends turned PINK. That's how good it staind my hair.
